sentences: Bob Carroll (June 8, 1918 – November 12, 1994) was an American big band singer and stage, film, and television actor.
Carroll's singing career was interrupted by three years' service in the U.S. Army during World War II.
Carroll also sang with other orchestras, including Charlie Barnet and Glenn Miller in the 1940s and Gordon Jenkins (for whom he recorded the hit "Charmaine" in 1951) in the 1950s.
